[0.002, "o", "\u001b[1;15Hh\u001b[3;4Hhe following modules are loaded before any boot \u001b[30m\u001b[103mho\u001b[4;31H\u001b[m\u000fh\u001b[5;7Hh\u001b[6;19Hhid xhci_h\u001b[10;4Hh\u001b[11;6Hh into the CPIO image.  Th\u001b[12;13Hhe actual binaries included by a given \u001b[30m\u001b[103mho\u001b[17;4H\u001b[m\u000fhis setting is similar to BINARIES above, \u001b[30m\u001b[103mho\u001b[18;42H\u001b[m\u000fh\u001b[22;4Hhis is the most important setting in this file.  The HOOKS control th\u001b[23;33Hhe image, and what h\u001b[24;46Hhat you do not change th\u001b[25;13Hhich HOOKS are added.  Run 'mkinitcpio -H <\u001b[30m\u001b[103mho\u001b[26;3H\u001b[m\u000fhelp on a given \u001b[30m\u001b[103mho\u001b[27;51H\u001b[m\u000fh\u001b[31;7Hhis setup specifies all modules in th\u001b[35;7Hhis setup will autodetect all modules for your system and s\u001b[30m\u001b[103mho\u001b[39;7H\u001b[m\u000fhis setup will generate a 'full' image which\u001b[43;7Hhis setup assembles a mdadm array with\u001b[47;157H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f6\u001b[48;4H\u001b[?25h"]
